        content4: 'Vaccines also protect future generations. Just like we are no longer at risk of smallpox, thanks to vaccines, in the future, we may be able to wipe out other diseases, like polio and measles. To eliminate these diseases in the future, we need high vaccination rates now. If you choose not to vaccinate or to delay vaccines, it\'s important that you understand the risks and responsibilities.',
